Mercedes-Benz Navigation DVD upgrade for NTG4-204 C-Class 204, SLS AMG

C-Klasse T-Model S204: >12/2007 - <02/2011 
C-Klasse Limousine W204: >03/2007 - <02/2011 
GLK-Klasse X204: >10/2008 - <05/2012 
SLS-Klasse R197 (Topless): >11/2011 
SLS-Klasse Coupe C197: >03/2010 

See picture

Use IMGBURN or Alcohol 120% to burn cue file / img file to disk

Burn DVD 1 on a DVD+DL Verbatim 8.5GB disk at 4x speed or 8x speed.
Burn DVD 2 on a Regular DVD-R or DVD+R 4.7GB DVD (Brand doesn't really matter as long as you burn at 4x speed just don't be cheap when buying empty dvd, I used Verbatim, JVC, Maxell, Variox and all worked well)

This update takes a couple hours, put the car on a charger or make a long drive, and sometimes click on the knob to let it get out if idle if the screen goes black (This only happens if the car is on a charger and engine is turned off)
